== Overview == The Tsukida Kofun Cluster comprises 35–40 Kofuns located in {{ill|Kasukawa Town Tsukida|ja|粕川町月田|12=draft}} and {{ill|Kasukawa Town Murozawa|ja|粕川町室沢|12=draft}} in Maebashi City, but most of these have already been destroyed.{{Sfn|Kojima|1982|loc=序}}{{Sfn|Kasukawa Village History Compilation Committee|1972|p=35}} Between 1948 and 1955, six mounds were excavated by {{ill|Kisao Ozaki|ja|尾崎喜左雄|12=draft}} and the Gunma University Archaeology Department.{{Sfn|Kojima|1982|p=16}} These mounds were dated from the late 6th century to the late 7th century.{{Sfn|Kasukawa Village History Compilation Committee|1972|p=48}} Later investigations in 1980–1981 by the Kasukawa Village Education Board indicated a predominance of mounds constructed in the late 7th century.{{Sfn|Kojima|1982|p=16}}
Two kofun in the cluster have been designated as prefectural historic sites: * '''Kagamitezuka Kofun''' - Gunma Prefecture Historic Site (designated February 8, 1949) * '''Danzuka Kofun''' - Gunma Prefecture Historic Site (designated October 5, 1951){{Cite web|title=List of Prefectural Cultural Properties|url=https://www.city.maebashi.gunma.jp/soshiki/kyoiku/bunkazaihogo/gyomu/3/2/5107.html|website=City of Maebashi|access-date=2024-04-21|language=ja}}
