'''Tsukida Kofun Cluster''' (月田古墳群) is a group of [[kofun]] (ancient Kofuns) from the late [[Kofun period]] located in {{ill|Maebashi|ja|前橋市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Gunma Prefecture|ja|群馬県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Japan, specifically in {{ill|Kasukawa Town Tsukida|ja|粕川町月田|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Kasukawa Town Murozawa|ja|粕川町室沢|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
== Overview == The Tsukida Kofun Cluster comprises 35–40 Kofuns located in {{ill|Kasukawa Town Tsukida|ja|粕川町月田|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Kasukawa Town Murozawa|ja|粕川町室沢|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in Maebashi City, but most of these have already been destroyed.{{Sfn|Kojima|1982|loc=序}}{{Sfn|Kasukawa Village History Compilation Committee|1972|p=35}} Between 1948 and 1955, six mounds were excavated by {{ill|Kisao Ozaki|ja|尾崎喜左雄|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and the Gunma University Archaeology Department.{{Sfn|Kojima|1982|p=16}} These mounds were dated from the late 6th century to the late 7th century.{{Sfn|Kasukawa Village History Compilation Committee|1972|p=48}} Later investigations in 1980–1981 by the Kasukawa Village Education Board indicated a predominance of mounds constructed in the late 7th century.{{Sfn|Kojima|1982|p=16}}
Two kofun in the cluster have been designated as prefectural historic sites: * '''Kagamitezuka Kofun''' - Gunma Prefecture Historic Site (designated February 8, 1949) * '''Danzuka Kofun''' - Gunma Prefecture Historic Site (designated October 5, 1951){{Cite web|title=List of Prefectural Cultural Properties|url=https://www.city.maebashi.gunma.jp/soshiki/kyoiku/bunkazaihogo/gyomu/3/2/5107.html|website=City of Maebashi|access-date=2024-04-21|language=ja}}
== List of Main Kofun == {| class="wikitable" style="font-size:small;width:60%" |+ Details of Major Kofun ! Kofun Name{{Sfn|Gunma Kofun Catalog|ja|群馬県古墳綜覧}} ! Catalog Number{{Sfn|Gunma Kofun Catalog|ja|上毛古墳綜覧}} ! Size ! Shape ! Burial Structure ! Location ! Excavation ! Notes |- ! Kagamitezuka Kofun ! Kasukawa 44 | 28 m | {{ill|Keyhole-shaped kofun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|qq=draft|qq=draft}} | Single-shoulder horizontal stone chamber | Kasukawa Town Tsukida 213 | 1948 | Designated prefectural historic site (February 8, 1949) |- ! Danzuka Kofun ! Kasukawa 36 | 25 m | Round mound | Horizontal stone chamber | Kasukawa Town Tsukida 207 | 1950 | Designated prefectural historic site (October 5, 1951) |} (Additional rows omitted for brevity)
== Surrounding Area == * {{ill|Chikado Shrine (Maebashi)|ja|近戸神社 (前橋市粕川町月田)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * {{ill|Yamashiro Multi-story Tower|ja|山上多重塔|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
